<item>
            <title>[LU-7896] lu_object_limit() is called too frequently</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7896</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;with ZFS the number of objects in LU cache is limited, so any lu_object_new() checks whether the limit is exceeded. so, at some point it&apos;s called for every new object and worse - many threads got blocked in lu_site_purge() due to that. we don&apos;t need that strong semantics for the number of cached object, this should be fixed in a way to purge objects in batches in non-blocking manner.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
